==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Skilligalee
<hw>Skil`li*ga*lee"</hw> <pr>(sk⟦icr⟧l`l⟦icr⟧*g⟦adot⟧*l⟦emac⟧")</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind of thin, weak broth or oatmeal porridge,
served out to prisoners and paupers in England; also, a drink made of
oatmeal, sugar, and water, sometimes used in the English navy or
army.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>skilligolee</asp>,
<asp>skillygalee</asp>, etc.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skilling</ent>⟦br⟧
